 a nickname from a variant of <i>mal</i> ‘bad’ (see   Mau  ), or a habitational name from a place called Maux or perhaps Meaux (see 2 below)."],"variants":[{"name":"Mau","meanings":["North German: nickname for a dandy or an affluent person, from Middle Low German <i>mouwe</i> ‘sleeve’, referring to a wide sleeve of expensive, ornamented fabric.","Portuguese: nickname from <i>mau</i> ‘bad, evil’ (from Latin <i>malus</i>).","French: nickname from a variant of <i>mal</i> ‘bad’."]}]},{"name":"Isabell","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."],"variants":[{"name":"Isabelle","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , now in frequent use in the English-speaking world."]},{"name":"Isobella","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."]},{"name":"Isobelle","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]},{"name":"Isobel","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Isabel ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Isabell Meaux was born in 1303, in Levisham, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Sir Geoffrey Meaux. She had at least 2 sons with William Percehay. She died before 1384, in Devon, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1303–before 1384":"1303–enne 1384","1303–1384":"1303–1384","1309–1377":"1309–1377","1297–1386":"1297–1386","1329–1383":"1329–1383","–1399":"–1399","1280–1310":"1280–1310","1297":"1297","1384":"1384","1383":"1383","Abt 1329":"umbes 1329","1280":"1280","1303":"1303","1399":"1399","1377":"1377","1310":"1310","1386":"1386","before 1384":"enne 1384","1309":"1309","1329":"1329","Kitton, Devon,England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Levisham, Yorkshire, England":"Levisham, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hestercombe, Somersetshire, England":"Hestercombe, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Burlescombe, Devon, England":"Burlescombe, Devon, England"},"fi":{"1303–before 1384":"1303–ennen vuotta 1384","1303–1384":"1303–1384","1309–1377":"1309–1377","1297–1386":"1297–1386","1329–1383":"1329–1383","–1399":"–1399","1280–1310":"1280–1310","1297":"1297","1384":"1384","1383":"1383","Abt 1329":"noin 1329","1280":"1280","1303":"1303","1399":"1399","1377":"1377","1310":"1310","1386":"1386","before 1384":"ennen vuotta 1384","1309":"1309","1329":"1329","Kitton, Devon,England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Levisham, Yorkshire, England":"Levisham, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hestercombe, Somersetshire, England":"Hestercombe, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Burlescombe, Devon, England":"Burlescombe, Devon, England"},"fr":{"1303–before 1384":"1303–avant 1384","1303–1384":"1303–1384","1309–1377":"1309–1377","1297–1386":"1297–1386","1329–1383":"1329–1383","–1399":"–1399","1280–1310":"1280–1310","1297":"1297","1384":"1384","1383":"1383","Abt 1329":"environ 1329","1280":"